  {
    "type": "EXEGETICAL (ORIGINAL LANGUAGES)",
    "name": "Pulpit Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_sub_title",
        "text": "Verse 3.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " - ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_word",
        "text": "And he did that which was right in the sight of the Lord, yet not like David his father.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " Only one King of Judah hitherto, viz. Asa, had obtained the praise that he \"did that which was right in the eyes of the Lord, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "accented",
        "text": "as did David his father\"",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "1 Kings 15:11",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "). All the others had fallen short more or less; and Amaziah fell short in many respects. He was wanting in \"a perfect heart\" (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "2 Chronicles 25:2",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "), ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "accented",
        "text": "i.e.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " a fixed intention to do God's will; he was proud and boastful (ver. 10); he gave way to idolatry in his later years (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "2 Chronicles 25:14",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "), and he despised the reproof of the prophet who was sent to rebuke his sin (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "2 Chronicles 25:16",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "). Though placed among the \"good kings' by the authors of both Kings and Chronicles, it is, as it were, under protest, with a distinct intimation that, although better than most of his predecessors, he did not reach a high standard. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_word",
        "text": "He did according to all things as Joash his father did.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " There is something of Oriental hyperbole in this statement, which must be understood in the spirit, not in the letter. The two kings were differently circumstanced, and history did not \"repeat itself\" in their reigns. The position of Joash with respect to Jehoiada finds no parallel in the circumstances of the life of Amaziah. Still, the lives are parallel to some extent. Both kings began better than they ended. Both were zealous for Jehovah at first, but turned to idolatry at last. Both opposed themselves to prophets, and treated their rebukes with scorn. Both reused conspiracy against them by their misconduct, and were murdered by the malcontents. Further, both were unsuccessful in war, had to withstand a siege of their capital, and bought off their enemy by the surrender of the greater part of its wealth, including the treasures of the temple (comp. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "2 Kings 12:18",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " with ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "2 Kings 14:14",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "). 2 Kings 14:3",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
  },
